## 1. `Vector` 기반 스레드 안전 큐 구현

### 구현 목표
- 내부 저장소: `java.util.Vector<E>`
- 다중 생산자/다중 소비자 환경에서 안전하게 동작
- `wait()/notifyAll()`을 이용한 blocking queue 형태 지원
- `ConcurrentModificationException` 유발 가능성을 낮추기 위해 외부에 내부 컬렉션 직접 노출 금지
- 반복 시에는 스냅샷 기반 조회 제공

### 코드

```java
import java.util.Vector;
import java.util.ArrayList;
import java.util.List;
import java.util.NoSuchElementException;

public final class VectorBasedBlockingQueue<E> {
    private final Vector<E> storage = new Vector<>();
    private final int capacity;

    public VectorBasedBlockingQueue(int capacity) {
        if (capacity <= 0) {
            throw new IllegalArgumentException("capacity must be > 0");
        }
        this.capacity = capacity;
    }

    public synchronized void enqueue(E element) throws InterruptedException {
        if (element == null) {
            throw new NullPointerException("null elements are not allowed");
        }

        while (storage.size() >= capacity) {
            wait();
        }

        storage.add(element);
        notifyAll();
    }

    public synchronized E dequeue() throws InterruptedException {
        while (storage.isEmpty()) {
            wait();
        }

        E value = storage.remove(0);
        notifyAll();
        return value;
    }

    public synchronized E peek() {
        if (storage.isEmpty()) {
            throw new NoSuchElementException("queue is empty");
        }
        return storage.get(0);
    }

    public synchronized int size() {
        return storage.size();
    }

    public synchronized boolean isEmpty() {
        return storage.isEmpty();
    }

    public synchronized List<E> snapshot() {
        return new ArrayList<>(storage);
    }

    public int capacity() {
        return capacity;
    }
}
```

---

## 2. 사용 예시

```java
public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        VectorBasedBlockingQueue<String> queue = new VectorBasedBlockingQueue<>(5);

        Thread producer = new Thread(() -> {
            try {
                for (int i = 1; i <= 10; i++) {
                    queue.enqueue("data-" + i);
                    System.out.println("Produced: data-" + i);
                }
            } catch (InterruptedException e) {
                Thread.currentThread().interrupt();
            }
        });

        Thread consumer = new Thread(() -> {
            try {
                for (int i = 1; i <= 10; i++) {
                    String item = queue.dequeue();
                    System.out.println("Consumed: " + item);
                }
            } catch (InterruptedException e) {
                Thread.currentThread().interrupt();
            }
        });

        producer.start();
        consumer.start();
    }
}
```

